Chelsea have signed teenager Dylan Williams from Derby County. On Friday, The Athletic reported that Chelsea had made a transfer offer for the 18-year-old full-back, which had been accepted. This is Chelsea’s first signing of the window. At Least 48 Dead In ISIS Prison Clashes Omicron Wave Leaves US Food Banks Scrambling For Volunteers Williams posted on Instagram on Saturday to say: “Wow. I am absolutely delighted to have signed for one of the biggest clubs in the world. “Thank you so much for everything the staff and players have done at Derby County. I cannot wait to get started at Chelsea.” Chelsea have not yet confirmed his signing, while the size of their offer has not been confirmed by Derby’s administrators Quantuma, who are in charge of the financially-stricken Championship club’s transfer business. Derby manager Wayne Rooney said on Friday: “We have agreed a fee with a Premier League club for Dylan Williams. “I couldn’t stand in the way of his opportunity.” POLL Chelsea plan to involve him in their Under-23 side should they complete his signing this month. Williams has made eight appearances for Derby this season. Derby are 23rd in the Championship, eight points away from safety. They have had 21 points deducted this season.